1
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,660
I'm talking to you, Wu Wei.

2
00:01:34,759 --> 00:01:36,640
Did a year out there make you dumb?

3
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:40,680
Thank you, Mr. Gu. Thank you, Mr. Qin.

4
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,360
Don't rush to thank us two.

5
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:44,420
Do you know who transferred you back?

6
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,360
China Aerospace.

7
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:47,720
Xu Xu.

8
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,640
Because the current rendezvous and docking plan

9
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,320
adopted your previous idea.

10
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:52,810
Because of this,

11
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:55,539
Xu Xu spent a lot of time persuading the leaders.

12
00:01:56,479 --> 00:01:57,940
You'd better not thank me.

13
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,410
Let's be practical.

14
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,440
Buy me a meal.

15
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,200
Today

16
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,280
is already our seventh test.

17
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,060
Still not good enough.

18
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,940
Everyone, we need to hurry up.

19
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,840
I think

20
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:20,680
although we cannot capture

21
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,440
the signal in the blackout zone,

22
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:23,560
we can have the ocean-going flight control team

23
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,680
use their shipborne monopulse radar

24
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,840
and photoelectric theodolite for capture and tracking.

25
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:30,200
Then sync the position and data of the reentry module

26
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,000
to all flight control stations.

27
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,600
This way,

28
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:34,240
as soon as the reentry module passes through the blackout zone,

29
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:36,840
we can capture it.

30
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,040
The method is fine.

31
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,600
But

32
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:40,560
the window for tracking and capture is only three minutes.

33
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:43,020
The flight control difficulty is very high.

34
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:44,720
But using monopulse radar,

35
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:46,360
the search beam is quite narrow.

36
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,000
Plus, the reentry module

37
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,240
has no ground-to-space response signal.

38
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,520
It can only be tracked by the reflection signal

39
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,960
from the plasma shell.

40
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,920
The surface of the plasma shell is very irregular,

41
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:56,360
and the reflection signal fluctuates greatly,

42
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:58,000
so stable tracking is impossible.

43
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,840
It can only serve as an auxiliary method.

44
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,480
Using photoelectric tracking equipment to track

45
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:03,760
is like using the naked eye

46
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,760
through a telescope

47
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,960
to find a high-speed meteor in the sky.

48
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:08,120
The reentry module's speed is so fast,

49
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,280
capture is extremely difficult.

50
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:12,120
With such a short time of three minutes,

51
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,960
how can it be captured?

52
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,140
The points you mentioned,

53
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,000
I have considered them all.

54
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:17,880
It's just...

55
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:18,600
Go on.

56
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:23,720
Hello?

57
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,000
So we need an extra layer of guarantee.

58
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,720
Okay, I understand.

59
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:34,060
I just received a notice from the Space Monitoring and Early Warning Center.

60
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:41,120
They predict solar flare activity

61
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,840
with a high probability of periodic outbreaks.

62
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:45,720
Ground signals will be interfered with by electromagnetic storms.

63
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:48,079
Everyone, we need a contingency plan

64
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:49,440
and to be fully prepared.

65
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,100
The mission might be delayed.

66
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,440
If it gets delayed,

67
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:03,080
we will miss another window.

68
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:06,440
The data inside the blackout zone,

69
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,720
we admittedly don't have.

70
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,960
But the data before entering the blackout zone,

71
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,680
we have it very completely.

72
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:18,010
What we need to do is actually very simple.

73
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,880
What we need to do is actually very simple.

74
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:23,080
Have every flight control station use their data

75
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:25,360
to estimate the returner's trajectory.

76
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:28,920
They should notify each other and compare results

77
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:32,240
to minimize the error.

78
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,720
You mean

79
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,560
we should compare with each other

80
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:39,159
to calculate the trajectory and landing site?

81
00:04:39,159 --> 00:04:41,360
This way, even if the optical-electronic theodolite loses it,

82
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:42,480
we can recapture it

83
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,520
the moment it breaks out of the blackout zone.

84
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,360
That's right.

85
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:48,800
Our spacecraft has a certain degree of protection against electromagnetic waves.

86
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:52,330
We can also prepare contingency plans for autonomous docking.

87
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,200
Mr. Gu.

88
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,890
Do you think it's feasible?

89
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:57,960
Very good.

90
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:00,840
Please continue.

91
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,600
I

92
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,520
will go send a message to Mr. Qin.

93
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:10,620
Did you write it all down just now?

94
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,920
Everyone, listen up.

95
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,920
I announce that from now on,

96
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,680
we are entering joint combat mode.

97
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:23,680
Old Qin and I will stay with you

98
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,360
until we crack this hard nut.

99
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,120
Yes.

100
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,640
Uh, Old Qin.

101
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:32,600
Uh.

102
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:35,520
Keep it up.

103
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:38,480
Keep it up.

104
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,880
Keep it up.

105
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:41,840
Qin,

106
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:43,920
you seem off today.

107
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,000
What's wrong?

108
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,360
No. I asked you

109
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,920
to encourage everyone,

110
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,920
and say a few words.

111
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,560
Why are you being so quiet?

112
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,120
What for?

113
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:55,240
Look at everyone's mood.

114
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,480
Did your words encourage them?

115
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,200
Do you know that?

116
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,720
Anxiety is actually a kind of pulse wave.

117
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,520
It can interfere with signals

118
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:05,920
and cause an emotional blackout zone, understand?

119
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,640
Then I'd rather have more anxiety

120
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,840
to strengthen the photoelectric signals

121
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:09,840
and penetrate the blackout zone.

122
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:13,040
It's better than scratching our heads and working hard here.

123
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:13,970
Photoelectric.

124
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:15,680
Theodolite.

125
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,520
That's one way to do it.

126
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,800
But I still don't want to see you scratching your head all day.

127
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:24,160
Even if you scratch, you should scratch happily.

128
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,800
These two are bickering again.

129
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,600
I'm used to it.

130
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,400
How do you scratch? Let me see.

131
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,200
Can scratching your head

132
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,280
be done in a fancy way?

133
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:31,600
You can scratch like this.

134
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,560
Bah! That's a monkey.

135
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,159
You old thing,

136
00:06:36,159 --> 00:06:38,020
always finding ways to insult me.

137
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:40,600
Your skills are inferior to a monkey's.

138
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,659
Wu Wei, what are you doing?

139
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,520
Wu Wei, what are you laughing at?

140
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,800
Why are you scratching your head?

141
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,520
Hurry up.

142
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,860
Mr. Gu, Mr. Qin.

143
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,400
I have an idea.

144
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,480
Regarding the signal problem of the return capsule,

145
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,800
can we use an optoelectronic theodolite

146
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,120
to capture and track it?

147
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,000
This would solve

148
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,800
the signal capture problem of the return capsule.

149
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,480
He's right.

150
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,130
And paired with a monopulse radar.

151
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,680
This method works.

152
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,760
Come up with a plan tonight,

153
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:16,000
and conduct joint testing based on the parameters.

154
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:16,800
No problem.

155
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,280
Well then.

156
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:28,000
What your Mr. Qin means is that

157
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,840
he will go out now

158
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,640
to buy you milk tea and coffee

159
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,480
and treat you all. Sound good?

160
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:36,960
Okay.

161
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:39,320
When did I say it was my treat?

162
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,320
Okay, my treat.

163
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:42,600
My treat.

164
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,040
Come on, let's give him a round of applause.

165
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,320
Thank you, Mr. Qin.

166
00:07:46,159 --> 00:07:47,360
I'll treat everyone.

167
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:12,840
How is his condition?

168
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,480
Judging from the test results,

169
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,920
Mr. Qin's cancer has relapsed.

170
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,760
Moreover,

171
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:25,090
it has spread to his liver and lymph nodes.

172
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,890
Surgery is no longer an option.

173
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:38,000
How much time does Qin have left?

174
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:40,640
A few months.

175
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,640
Or it could

176
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,039
worsen at any time.

177
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:46,120
During this time,

178
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,040
try to keep him comfortable.

179
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,640
Do you still remember

180
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:19,600
the question Qin brought up?

181
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,250
I think I figured it out,

182
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:40,610
but I'm not sure.

183
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:45,600
Qin asked us before too.

184
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:48,760
Do you have an answer now?

185
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:52,920
Perhaps.

186
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,680
But this answer

187
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,330
is different for everyone.

188
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,930
I only know that meaningful things

189
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,800
are never easy.

190
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:12,580
I don't know about the answer,

191
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,480
but it reminds me of a quote

192
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,040
by my idol, Carl Sagan.

193
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:21,290
Looking back from the eternal,

194
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,560
all-encompassing dark universe.

195
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,560
You will see an

196
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:28,720
unremarkable pale blue dot.

197
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:30,520
That's here.

198
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:32,480
Earth.

199
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:35,000
Everything we are.

200
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,240
Everyone you love,

201
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:41,360
everyone you know,

202
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:43,280
everyone you ever heard of,

203
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:46,280
lived out their lives on it.

204
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:50,520
All our joy and suffering,

205
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,480
love, hate, and parting,

206
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,370
every young couple in love,

207
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,560
parents and teachers,

208
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,480
hopeful children,

209
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:05,280
scientists, and explorers,

210
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,280
are all here.

211
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,760
Go on.

212
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,680
This is Wenchang Space Launch Site.

213
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:42,040
The Zhengtu-5 Y5 carrier rocket

214
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:44,480
and the Haoyue-5 lunar probe

215
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,760
have been vertically transported to the launch area.

216
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:49,560
It is scheduled between 4:00 a.m. and 5:00 a.m. on the 24th

217
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:51,880
to carry out the launch mission at an opportune time.

218
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:53,040
Aerospace Flight Control Center,

219
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,640
Wenchang Space Launch Site,

220
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,280
Xi'an Flight Control,

221
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,760
Yuanwang tracking fleet,

222
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:59,440
and various flight control stations for the mission.

223
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,920
We have fully completed

224
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:03,450
all mission preparations before the launch.

225
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,320
Attention, all stations.

226
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,580
Two minutes to launch.

227
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,410
Ten-second countdown.

228
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:43,240
Nine.

229
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,120
Six.

230
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,240
Five.

231
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:48,880
Four.

232
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,160
Three.

233
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:53,800
Ignition.

234
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:57,440
Liftoff.

235
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:04,800
Liftoff time,

236
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:07,520
04:30

237
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:10,440
and 21.806 seconds.

238
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:21,540
Wenchang optical radar tracking is normal.

239
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:23,370
Telemetry signals are normal.

240
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,730
Wenchang flight is normal.

241
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:29,120
Programmed turn.

242
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:33,260
Wenchang optical radar tracking is normal.

243
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,730
Telemetry signals are normal.

244
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,480
Wenchang flight is normal.

245
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:52,600
Booster shutdown.

246
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,240
Booster separation.

247
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:57,660
Fairing jettison.

248
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,600
First and second stage separation.

249
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,520
Second stage, secondary shutdown.

250
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,840
Spacecraft and rocket separation.

251
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,180
Solar panel deployed.

252
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:33,800
Wenchang announces successful launch.

253
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:40,320
Great.

254
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:44,240
We made it.

255
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:45,280
Good.

256
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,880
Then launch it.

257
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:12,360
I watched it from beginning to end.

258
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:14,800
Good job.

259
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,040
Rest assured.

260
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:24,000
The orbit entry went smoothly.

261
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,330
Now we're just waiting for the next phase.

262
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,440
Next, we will enter

263
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,960
the closed period for the lunar landing mission.

264
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:33,000
We came specifically to let you know.

265
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:33,800
Rest assured.

266
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,400
We will definitely complete the mission well.

267
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:50,240
Good job.

268
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:56,640
I have a better eye

269
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:57,360
than Mr. Gu.

270
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:04,000
You look more energetic with short hair.

271
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,000
Ziqi.

272
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:07,920
You must

273
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:13,920
bring the lunar soil back.

274
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:15,840
Rest assured.

275
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,080
I'll be waiting

276
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,810
to drink the celebration wine.

277
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:33,880
Oh, you.

278
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,280
I prepared grape juice for you.

279
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,080
No drinking.

280
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:39,600
Why? As long as we're celebrating,

281
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,320
anything we drink is wine.

282
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:44,600
What? Are you afraid I can't hold on?

283
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,760
I still want to dance in space.

284
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:50,120
You had a piece of your intestines cut out,

285
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,160
and you're still bragging.

286
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,680
Then I'll dance for you now.

287
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,840
Okay, you're not bragging.

288
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:54,840
That's enough.

